\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M44"><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>α</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>^</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>2.5566</mml:mn></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2015_577_IEq6.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and a goodness-of-fit parameter of <italic>R</italic>
<sup>2</sup>=0.9362.<fig id="Fig3"><label>Figure 3</label><caption><p>Fitting of degree distribution. The degree distribution of 50 networks generated with the same size is fitted by a line in log-log space. The resulting estimated scale parameter is <inline-formula id="IEq7"><alternatives><tex-math id="M45">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
